result.name: Istanbul Express Turkish Restaurant

reviews.text: Food was good but a bit on the "umami" side. I've been told that I enjoy bland food so maybe the average person would think the flavour is fine? I'd still like to come back here to try some other items on the menu since there aren't many restaurants like this.

Small modestly decorated restaurant, appears to be family run.

Ordered a Chicken shish kebab with salad and chips. Arrived quite promptly and was hot and quite tasty. Service was quick and polite.

The prices here were moderate and definitely worth another visit to sample their other kebabs on offer.

Decor looks like it's a typical local Hong Kong restaurant - feels like I am in  cheap eatery with bad wallpapers. Nothing from turkish decor, not even the plates.

As we came in, we looked for a table in the restaurant (it was 80% empty) but the waiter hastily sat us next to the exit and said "sit here". The service was non existent, we basically had to fight for our food not to be taken away, the waiter couldn't help himself but come over and try to clear our unfinished plates at least 3 times ( maybe they ran out of plates?). Nothing Turkish about this place besides the two people who work here and they don't even cook anything. The chef was sitting around in the dining area and watching tv - what a life! As we paid, the staff just handed the bill and the credit card without a single word. 

The food was mediocre at best. We had hummus which tasted watered down, no seasoning.. Everything else was greasy and not good at all. Do not trust the photos of the food on their menu, maybe this is what food looks like back at home in Turkey but not here....

Save yourself some money and time and go somewhere else.. Way to let down such an amazing cuisine and culture.

Best Turkish coffee in town!

Great kebabs. Their menu is extensive but from what I have tried I have no complaints.

The prices are very reasonable for being located right in the middle of the Wan Chai bar district!
My friend thinks that they have the best lentil soup in the world. So we go there a lot. I have always been satisfied with all the dishes that I have eaten there. Service is quick.

reviews.text: Food was good but a bit on the "umami" side. I've been told that I enjoy bland food so maybe the average person would think the flavour is fine? I'd still like to come back here to try some other items on the menu since there aren't many restaurants like this.
İstanbul'da yediğiniz lezzeti aramayın ama Çin yemeklerini yiyemiyorsanız sizi doyurmaya yetecek şeyler var.

Enteresan bir tecrübe, muhtemelen Hong Kong'ta bulunan en iyi Türk restaurantı diyebiliriz ancak ne hikmettir ki sahibi sizin Türk olduğunuzu anladığında konuşmaktan imtina ediyor. E madem öyle bizde yurdumuza gelmiş gibi hissettiğimiz bu restaurant içinde kadir kıymet göremiyorsak eksiklikleri gözardı etmeden yorumumuzu yapalım. 

Birincisi etlerin kalitesi, yani başka yerde de et yiyoruz Kobe beef dedikleri o eti önce bir tatsınlar arkasından o eti kullanıp Beyti, Adana vs mutfağımıza ait yemekleri yapsınlar. Evet HKK için bu bile fazla ama madem Türk mutfağı hizmeti veriyorlar hem de İstanbul gibi güzide bir şehrin adını kullanarak o zaman o yemeğin hakkını vereceksiniz arkadaş. Tadı bir değişik o etin. Beğenmedim açıkcası.

İkincisi içeriye Türk girdiğinde korkmayın sizi yemezler, değer verin, biz size değer verdiğimiz, yaptığınız işe saygı duyduğumuz ve memleket hasreti ile geliyoruz oraya.

Üç biraz daha temizliğe dikkat diyeceğim ama zaten orası Hong Kong gayet normal.

Kolay gelsin...
